---
import OfferingsLayout from "../../layouts/OfferingsLayout.astro";
import MainImage from "../../assets/offerings-group-sessions.jpg";
import Button from "../ui/inputs/Button.astro";
import InfoHighlightLayout from "../../layouts/InfoHighlightLayout.astro";
import Accordion from "../accordion/Accordion.astro";
import AccordionTitle from "../accordion/AccordionTitle.astro";
import AccordionContent from "../accordion/AccordionContent.astro";
---

<OfferingsLayout title="Group Sessions">
  <div
    class="w-full aspect-video lg:aspect-73/30 overflow-hidden border-8 border-flick-dark"
  >
    <img
      src={MainImage.src}
      alt="Group session"
      class="relative bottom-14 sm:bottom-25 lg:bottom-75 w-full object-cover aspect-4/3"
    />
  </div>
  <p class="font-light text-xl lg:text-2xl">
    Our level-based* group sessions are structured to balance quality coaching,
    focused training, and match play. Each two-hour session (max 12 players)
    includes a 15-minute warm-up, 1 hour 15 minutes of drill practice with water
    breaks, and 30 minutes of match play. Coaches provide personalised feedback
    to every player, with groups organised by level to ensure the right
    challenge and steady improvement.
  </p>
  <a href="https://bookwhen.com/flicktt" target="_blank" class="m-auto">
    <Button size="lg">Book now</Button>
  </a>
  <InfoHighlightLayout title="Group Coaching Levels (1-4)">
    <p class="font-semibold text-xl lg:text-2xl">
      Our group sessions are split by levels so you train at the right pace and
      improve faster. Levels are based on repeatable skills, not “who wins
      games”.
    </p>
    <p>
      Not sure where you fit? Book Level 1-2 or ask a coach on the day — we'll
      guide you to the best group for progress. (You'll also see Level 1-2 / 2-3
      / 3-4 sessions in the booking schedule.)
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <Accordion>
        <AccordionTitle>
          LEVEL 1 — Solid foundations (stance, grip, control)
        </AccordionTitle>
        <AccordionContent>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Perfect if:</span> you're new, returning
              after a break, or you can rally “sometimes” but don't feel in control.
            </p>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">We focus on</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                  Ready position (stance), balance and distance to the table
                </li>
                <li>Correct grip and racket angle</li>
                <li>Clean contact and simple, consistent strokes (no spin)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">You will learn</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>Forehand & backhand basics with a stable trajectory</li>
                <li>Simple placement (cross-court / down-the-line)</li>
                <li>
                  First consistency drills: keep the ball on the table with good
                  form
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">To move up to Level 2</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                  You can rally comfortably on both sides at a steady pace
                </li>
                <li>Your technique stays stable under light pressure</li>
                <li>
                  You understand and apply basic coaching corrections (distance,
                  angle, timing)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Main difference vs Level 2:</span> Level
              1 builds control. Level 2 adds real consistency with spin awareness.
            </p>
          </div>
        </AccordionContent>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion>
        <AccordionTitle>
          LEVEL 2 — Consistency + understanding spin
        </AccordionTitle>
        <AccordionContent>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Perfect if:</span> you can rally, but spin
              (especially serves) makes the ball fly long, drop in the net, or kick
              sideways.
            </p>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">We focus on</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>Stronger forehand/backhand consistency with placement</li>
                <li>Reading topspin / backspin / sidespin</li>
                <li>Basic receive so you stop giving away free points</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">You will learn</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>Controlled rallies with better depth and direction</li>
                <li>How to identify spin and adjust racket angle + timing</li>
                <li>Safer pushes and controlled returns against backspin</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">To move up to Level 2</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                  You can keep consistent rallies with intention (not just
                  “survive”)
                </li>
                <li>
                  You recognise common spins and react correctly most of the
                  time
                </li>
                <li>Your basics hold up in longer drills</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Main difference vs Level 3:</span> Level
              2 is “I understand spin.” Level 3 is “I can attack with topspin and
              defend with blocks.”
            </p>
          </div>
        </AccordionContent>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion>
        <AccordionTitle>
          LEVEL 3 — Topspin consistency + blocking + structured drills
        </AccordionTitle>
        <AccordionContent>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Perfect if:</span> you want to play modern
              table tennis: open the point, pressure, and hold rallies without breaking
              down.
            </p>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">We focus on</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>Reliable topspin (not occasional hero shots)</li>
                <li>Blocking technique (control + placement)</li>
                <li>
                  Structured multi-step drills (including 12-ball patterns)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">You will learn</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                  Forehand topspin consistency (and backhand topspin progression
                  when appropriate)
                </li>
                <li>Opening vs backspin (the key “next step” skill)</li>
                <li>Active blocks: control height, depth and direction</li>
                <li>
                  Longer patterns: rhythm, placement changes, and transitions
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">To move up to Level 2</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                  You can topspin safely with margin and repeat it in drills
                </li>
                <li>You can block without popping the ball up</li>
                <li>
                  You complete longer patterns with stable technique and
                  decisions
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Main difference vs Level 4:</span> Level
              3 builds your rally engine. Level 4 teaches you to win points from the
              serve + first 3 balls.
            </p>
          </div>
        </AccordionContent>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion>
        <AccordionTitle>
          LEVEL 4 — Serve + receive + “first 3 balls” (play with a plan)
        </AccordionTitle>
        <AccordionContent>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold">Perfect if:</span>you have good
              strokes, but points slip away on serve/receive, or you don't know
              what to do on 3rd/5th ball.
            </p>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">We focus on</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>Serve quality and variation with a purpose</li>
                <li>Receive that doesn't gift easy points</li>
                <li>
                  First 3 balls patterns: serve → receive → 3rd ball attack
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">You will learn</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                  Practical serve fundamentals (contact, control, disguise,
                  intention)
                </li>
                <li>
                  Useful variations: short/long, backspin/topspin/sidespin
                  mixes, float
                </li>
                <li>
                  Receive options (short/long push, controlled placement, basic
                  flick when suitable)
                </li>
                <li>
                  3rd ball attack with high percentage (repeatable, not risky)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">To move up to Level 2</span>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                <li>Your serves create predictable returns</li>
                <li>Your receive stays stable under pressure</li>
                <li>
                  Your 3rd ball attack is reliable and you can continue the
                  point with intent
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </AccordionContent>
      </Accordion>
    </div>
    <div>
      <span class="font-bold text-xl lg:text-2xl">
        QUICK SELF-CHECK (pick your starting level)
      </span>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">Level 1:</span> stance/grip basics + consistent
          simple hits (no spin)
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">Level 2:</span> consistent basics + understand
          spin, especially on serve/receive
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">Level 3:</span> consistent topspin + blocking
          + longer structured drills
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">Level 4:</span> serve/receive + strong first
          3 balls and opening attack
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </InfoHighlightLayout>
</OfferingsLayout>
